LiteSVM Testing Framework - Dual Licensing
==========================================

This project uses dual licensing to appropriately cover different types of content:

## Software Components (GPL-3.0-or-later)
All software code, including but not limited to:
- Rust source code (*.rs files)
- The litesvm-testing library
- Test frameworks and utilities
- Build scripts and configuration
- Compiled binaries and libraries

Licensed under: GNU General Public License v3.0 or later
License file: COPYING
License URL: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html

## Educational Content (CC BY-SA 4.0)
All educational and documentation materials, including but not limited to:
- Documentation files (*.md files)
- README files
- Tutorial content
- Example explanations and educational commentary
- Code comments explaining educational concepts

Licensed under: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International
License file: LICENSE-CONTENT  
License URL: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

## Why Dual Licensing?

- **GPL-3.0-or-later** ensures that improvements to the software remain open source
  and available to the community (copyleft protection)

- **CC BY-SA 4.0** makes educational content more accessible for teaching, learning,
  and integration into educational materials while still requiring attribution and
  keeping improvements open

## Questions?

If you're unsure which license applies to specific content, please refer to the
file type and purpose described above, or open an issue for clarification.

